"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"a17181",
"children":[
"Psychological screening for depression, anxiety, and somatization is an important adjunct to a thorough history and physical examination."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gm_s9_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"7392fd",
"children":[
"Evidence-based nondrug treatment most commonly includes:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"97e96b",
"children":[
"exercise"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"f77dac",
"children":[
"physical therapy"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"2c138e",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"cognitive behavioral therapy",
"children":[
"CBT"
]
},
" "
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"9e30b4",
"children":[
"Multimodal therapy is typically superior to single-modality therapy."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"5f0355",
"children":[
"Drug treatment for neuropathic pain includes:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"3a259c",
"children":[
"capsaicin cream or a lidocaine patch or cream"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"648b30",
"children":[
"gabapentin and pregabalin"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"7831d1",
"children":[
"tricyclic antidepressants"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"dcaba7",
"children":[
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"serotonin-norepinephrine reuptake inhibitor",
"children":[
"SNRI"
]
},
"s"
]
},
" (duloxetine and venlafaxine)"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f36a42",
"children":[
"Initial drug therapy for nociceptive pain is primarily ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs",
"children":[
"NSAIDs"
]
},
" (if an inflammatory component is present)."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"e6c89a",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"No evidence supports the efficacy of long-term opioids in managing chronic noncancer pain."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"b38edd",
"children":[
"Despite the lack of evidence for their efficacy, if opioids are used, the following should be done:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"be0ed8",
"children":[
"an assessment to evaluate for risk of abuse and diversion"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"504ebb",
"children":[
"written treatment agreements"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"fcb68e",
"children":[
"adherence monitoring (urine drug screens)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"b9f5e4",
"children":[
"surveillance using prescription monitoring programs"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"176bbd",
"children":[
"Do not concurrently prescribe opioids and benzodiazepines."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
}
]
